Maintainer: YuKi <hmz1969a@gmail.com>
Description: Provides a compact C++ backend for Approximate Bayesian
    Computation with a thin R frontend. The public R interface is intentionally
    small and centers on abc() and summary() methods, while the computational
    work is performed by shared C++ code. The package supports rejection ABC,
    regression-adjustment workflows, and optional PCA or PLS reduction of
    summary statistics. It is inspired by common ABC workflows and the R abc
    interface, but is organized as a shared backend rather than a direct
    user-interface copy of the abc package.
